ADULT FEMALE (
Fig. 5
). Living specimen : fully-grown reproductive females sub-spherical, dark red or brown, covered with a fine white or pale grey mealy wax; body 5 ( 3–7 ) mm long, 4.7 ( 2.7–6.6 ) mm wide and 4.6 ( 2.6–6 ) mm high (Plate 2 : a, b, c). Due to their heavily sclerotized cuticle, these are unsuitable for a reliable identification based on microscopic morphological characters. The following description is based on young pre-reproductive females.
